markdown: R.10/Add. 37 <::Scatter plot showing the relationship between LYSINE (g/16 g N) on the y-axis and an unlabeled x-axis, with values ranging from 0 to 4.0. A line of best fit is drawn through the data points, and the correlation coefficient is given as r = 0.994. The data points are labeled as follows: - BREAD: approximately (0.9, 2.6) - BREAD + OATMEAL: approximately (1.3, 3.7) - BREAD + EGG: approximately (2.2, 4.6) - BREAD + PROTEIN CEREAL + MILK: approximately (2.7, 4.6) - BREAD + BEANS: approximately (2.8, 5.0) - BREAD + CASEIN: approximately (3.0, 5.6) - BREAD + CHEESE: approximately (3.1, 5.8) - BREAD + FISH FLOUR: approximately (3.4, 6.2) : chart::> Fig. 5 - Supplementary effect of several foods when mixed with bread and fed at 5% protein from each. Data of McLaughlan and Morrison (39). Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/ylvd0228
